ay and expects `onCancel` to be called. Since `cancel()` calls `this.hide(() => 
{ this.dialogConfig.onCancel?.() })`, and `hide()` creates a tween with `onCompl
ete`, the MockTweenManager should call `onComplete` synchronously, which means `
onCancel` should be called.\n\nWait, but the test failed. Let me re-read the tes
t:\n```typescript\nit(\'should close on overlay when closeOnOverlay is true\', (
