.id}:`;\n  for (const key of eventHandlers.keys()) {\n    if (event) {\n      if
(key.startsWith(keyPrefix + event)) {\n        eventHandlers.delete(key);\n     
}\n    } else if (key.startsWith(keyPrefix)) {\n      eventHandlers.delete(key);
\n    }\n  }\n  return this;\n}\n```\n\nAnd `emit` in `MockRectangle`:\n```types
cript\nemit(event: string, ...args: unknown[]) {\n  emitEvent(this, event, ...ar
gs);\n  return this;\n}\n```\n\nSo `emitEvent` looks up handlers in `eventHandle
rs` using the object\'s id. This should work.\n\nWait, but the `MockRectangle` d
oesn\'t call `super.on()` - it overrides it completely. So the handler is stored
