id}:`;\n  for (const key of eventHandlers.keys()) {\n    if (event) {\n      if 
(key.startsWith(keyPrefix + event)) {\n        eventHandlers.delete(key);\n     
}\n    } else if (key.startsWith(keyPrefix)) {\n      eventHandlers.delete(key);
\n    }\n  }\n  return this;\n}\n```\n\nWait! There\'s a bug here! When iteratin
g over a Map and deleting keys during iteration, some keys might be skipped in J
avaScript! This is a known issue with `for...of` over Maps while deleting.\n\nAc
tually, in JavaScript, deleting entries from a Map during `for...of` iteration i
s safe according to the spec - the iterator will continue with the remaining ent
ries. But wait, that\'s for `Map.prototype.forEach`. For `for...of`, it might be
different.\n\nActually, according to the ECMAScript spec, deleting entries that 
